\sin^2x=1-\cos(x)
\sin^2x = 1 - \cos^2 x
\cos x
\sin^2x=1-\cos(x)\iff 1 - \cos^2x = 1 - \cos x 
\iff \cos^2 x - \cos x = 0 \iff \cos x(\cos x - 1) = 0
u = \cos x
u(u-1) = 0 \implies u = 0 \text{ or}\;u = 1
u = \cos x = 0 \; \implies\; x = \frac{(2k + 1)\pi}{2},\; k \in \mathbb Z
u =  \cos x = 1 \; \implies\; x = 2k\pi, \; k \in \mathbb Z
